{"lemma": "ظِلْفٌ", "slug": "ظِلْفٌ", "root": "ظ.ل.ف", "root_slug": "ظ-ل-ف", "root_link": "/words/roots/ظ-ل-ف", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n27624"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B8%D9%90%D9%84%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "hoof", "fa": "سمت", "ur": "ظِلْف (سمت)", "tr": "tırnak", "id": "kuku", "bn": "খুর", "es": "pezuña", "fr": "sabot", "de": "Huf", "ru": "копыто", "zh": "蹄"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "cloven hoof, hoof of an artiodactyl (even-toed ungulate)."}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/ðˤilf/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n27624", "headword_ar": "ظِلْفٌ", "root": "Zlf", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "The"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zufor", "text_ar": "ظُفْر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cloven hoof"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of any ruminant"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, M)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the bovine kind"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T;) [i. e.] it is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an appertenance of the bovine kind"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the sheep"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goat"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the gazelle"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "antelope"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, K) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which is to them like the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zufor", "text_ar": "ظُفْر"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to man,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "like the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qadam", "text_ar": "قَدَم"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to us:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) one says the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rijol", "text_ar": "رِجْل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qadam", "text_ar": "قَدَم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a man, and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAfir", "text_ar": "حَافِر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a horse, and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xuf~", "text_ar": "خُفّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a camel and of an ostrich, and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zilof", "text_ar": "ظِلْف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a bovine animal and of a sheep or goat [and the like]: (ISk, T, TA:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aZolaAfN", "text_ar": "اَظْلَافٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, O, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ZuluwfN", "text_ar": "ظُلُوفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, O, K:) and"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1919}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aZolaAf", "text_ar": "اَظْلَاف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is applied, by 'Amr Ibn-Maadee-kerib, to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hoofs of horses,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, O,) as is said by Lth and Az and IF, by poetic license, (O,) metaphorically: (S, O:) and by El-Akhtal, metaphorically, to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "feet of men."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, IB, TA.) [Its dual is used in the K, in explanations of the words"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aEirapN", "text_ar": "شَعِرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$oEaru", "text_ar": "اَشْعَرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the latter instance on the authority of Lh, as meaning The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "two halves of a cloven hoof."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] And one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA", "text_ar": "مَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ja$imotu A_ilayoka ZilofFA", "text_ar": "جَشِمْتُ اـِلَيْكَ ظِلْفًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[app. meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I have not had the trouble of bringing to thee"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so much as"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the hoof of a gazelle"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (AZ, TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "j$m", "text_ar": "جشم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa yaA^okuluhu biDirosK wayaTaw^uhu biZilofK", "text_ar": "هُوَ يَاْكُلُهُ بِضِرْسٍ وَيَطَوُهُ بِظِلْفٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He eats it with a lateral tooth, and treads it with a cloven hoof;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "app. meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "vehemently"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  It is sometimes used as meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Cloven-hoofed animals."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA", "text_ar": "مَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lahu xuf~N walaA HaAfirN walaA ZilofN", "text_ar": "لَهُ خُفٌّ وَلَا حَافِرٌ وَلَا ظِلْفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He possesses not camels, nor horses"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "asses"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mules, nor sheep"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goats"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "other cloven-hoofed beasts"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xf", "text_ar": "خف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b3-  It also signifies [or implies] The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "making consecutive progressions"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in walking and in other actions, (T, K,) or, accord. to the L, in a thing. (TA.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaA='ati AlA_ibilu EalaY ZilofK waAHidK", "text_ar": "جَا=ءَتِ الاـِبِلُ عَلَى ظِلْفٍ وَاحِدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, A, O, TA) i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The camels came following one another."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA. [See also a similar phrase voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xuf~N", "text_ar": "خُفٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ganamu fulaAnK ZilofK waAHidK", "text_ar": "غَنَمُ فُلَانٍ ظِلْفٍ وَاحِدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidK", "text_ar": "وَاحِدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ZalafK", "text_ar": "ظَلَفٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The sheep,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goats, of such a one, have all of them brought forth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[app."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one after another"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (M.) ―         -b4-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A thing that is suitable to the requirements"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a man, and of a beast: (M:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an object of desire:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, O, K:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an object of want."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, K.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSaAba", "text_ar": "اَصَابَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN Zilofahu", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ ظِلْفَهُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one attained what was suitable to his requirements,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what he desired:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and sometimes one says the like of any beast that finds, or lights on, or meets with, that which he likes. (M.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wajadati Ald~aAb~apu ZilofahaA", "text_ar": "وَجَدَتِ الدَّابَّةُ ظِلْفَهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a prov., (M, O,) applied to him who finds the means of attaining that which he seeks; (Meyd;) meaning ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The beast found what was suitable to its requirements;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what withheld it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from other things"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and prevented its desire"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thereof"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A, TA. [See also Freytag's Arab. Prov., ii. 807.]) And one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wajadati Al$~aApu ZilofahaA", "text_ar": "وَجَدَتِ الشَّاةُ ظِلْفَهَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The sheep,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goat, found suitable pasturage, and therefore did not quit it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA:) a prov. mentioned by Fr; applied to him, of men and of beasts, that finds what is suitable to him. (TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baladN mino Zilofi Alganami", "text_ar": "بَلَدٌ مِنْ ظِلْفِ الغَنَمِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A country of such as are suitable to sheep"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goats."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wajada Zilofahu", "text_ar": "وَجَدَ ظِلْفَهُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He found what he loved,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what he desired,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what was suitable to him;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;) said of a man. (O.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA wajadotu Einodahu ZilofiY", "text_ar": "مَا وَجَدْتُ عِنْدَهُ ظِلْفِى"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I did not find with him the object of my want."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)       -A2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ZalofN", "text_ar": "ظَلْفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", near the middle of the paragraph. ―         -b2-  [In some copies of the K,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlZ~ilofu", "text_ar": "الظِّلْفُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is erroneously put for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlZ~alafu", "text_ar": "الظَّلَفُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as relating to the means of subsistence. And in the CK"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ZilofuhaA", "text_ar": "ظِلْفُهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is erroneously put for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ZalifuhaA", "text_ar": "ظَلِفُهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zalifu Aln~afosi", "text_ar": "ظَلِفُ النَّفْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]"}], "source_refs": ["T", "M", "S", "O", "Msb", "K", "ISk", "TA", "A"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}